28/01/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Greece's foreign policy interests are indivisibly connected to those of the EU, Foreign Minister George Papandreou said Tuesday (27 January).
He added that the major guidelines for Greek foreign policy are integrity, peace and co-operation.
The country is also working for cohesion and solidarity within the Union, he told the EU foreign ministers meeting in Brussels.
(MPA - 27/01/04)
